properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 11 at 2:51PM CST until February 12 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Grand Forks ND
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions expected. Total snow accumulations of
one to 2 inches. Winds gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of west central Minnesota and southeast North
Dakota.

* WHEN...From 5 AM to 3 PM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Widespread blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
dangerously cold wind chills as low as 40 below zero could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes. The
dangerous wind chills will last beyond the blowing snow into
Thursday morning.
properties.instruction:
Travel should be restricted to emergencies only. If you must
travel, have a winter survival kit with you. If you get stranded,
stay with your vehicle.

The latest road conditions for North Dakota can be found at
dot.nd.gov/travel and for Minnesota at 511mn.org, or by calling
5 1 1 in either state.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 5 AM TO 3 PM CST WEDNESDAY
